full stop.en-uk:
punctuation mark used at the end of a sentence, sometimes used in speech 
for emphasis ("Whom does he support? Arsenal, full stop!") (US: period, 
q.v.)

government.en-us:
the collective agency through which government is exercised (UK: the state
