)

tube.en-uk:
(often cap.) the London subterranean railway system ("the London Underground"); 
(sometimes incorrectly applied to that of other cities, e.g. "the Berlin 
tube")

yankee, yank.en-us:
(n.)1. A patriot from the American Revolution;
2. a New Englander; in the South, someone from the Northern US (often 
disparaging). A Minnesotan would not consider himself a Yankee or use the 
word regularly, but would consider someone from Connecticut to be a yankee; 
a Texan would consider both yankees, but not himself, and would be much 
more likely to use the word;
3. a player for the New York Yankees baseball team
